Here’s a short, crisp version (perfect for GitHub or slides):
🧠 Key Design Decisions (Short)
Dataset-driven: Uses input data as the single source of truth, no assumptions
Global reasoning: Validates flows using cross-dataset topology, not just row-level data
QM-first matching: Prioritizes Queue Manager alignment over queue-name matching
Clear ambiguity handling: Classifies flows (e.g., QM_ONLY_MATCH, MULTI_CANDIDATE) for controlled decisions
Canonical target design: Enforces one QM per app with standardized routing patterns
Safe automation: Includes valid flows, excludes uncertain ones, avoids wrong assumptions
Human-in-loop: Flags ambiguous flows as needs_review instead of rejecting them
Explainable decisions: Every transformation is traceable with reasons and confidence
